{"article_id":"pRbhWxbI39ggINVJ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Sen. Jeff Flake is serious about making Republicans vote on a bill","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"to protect Robert Mueller .","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"Two weeks ago , Flake said","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"that he would block all judicial nominees on the floor and in committee","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"unless a bill","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"protecting special counsel Robert Mueller","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"received a Senate floor vote .","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"And he proved","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"that he was keen to follow through in a series of moves this week .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"On Wednesday , Flake voted against advancing controversial nominee Thomas Farr , a North Carolina lawyer","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"who is up for a district court spot ,","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"during a Senate floor vote .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"And since then , Judiciary Chair Chuck Grassley canceled a committee meeting","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"that would have included votes on more than 20 judicial nominees ,","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"apparently due to Flake ' s key vote in committee .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell has been clear","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"that , aside from any spending bills , Republicans ' priority for the end of the year is to keep pushing judges through","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"- and","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"if Flake holds on this issue ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"it could throw a wrench into that plan .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"But it ' s not clear just how aggressive Flake is willing to be .","depth":4},{"id":21,"text":"On Thursday , he withdrew his opposition to a judicial nominee for the Eighth Circuit , a move","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"he said","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"was to balance out the absence of Sen. James Inhofe","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"( R-OK ) ,","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"who was called away for family reasons ,","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"according to the Washington Post .","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"Senators sometimes do this ,","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"as Sen. Lisa Murkowski famously did during Brett Kavanaugh ' s confirmation","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"when she withdrew her vote","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"and was marked as \" present . \"","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"In the waning days of Flake ' s presence in the Senate , the Arizona lawmaker ,","depth":5},{"id":32,"text":"who ' s frequently clashed with Trump ,","depth":5},{"id":33,"text":"now has dwindling opportunities","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"to make his mark .","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"Longtime observers of his tortured reluctance","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"to back Republicans","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"going in a direction","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"he does not like","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"will recall","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"that such stands often end with Flake simply , well , flaking .","depth":5},{"id":41,"text":"It remains to be seen if he ' ll live up to that standard one last time .","depth":4},{"id":42,"text":"Flake has said","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"he won ' t back any judicial nominees","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"until he sees a floor vote on legislation","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"that protects special counsel Robert Mueller and his investigation into Russian election interference .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"It ' s an ultimatum","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"that hits at Republicans ' narrow margins in the Senate","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"( which will be wider","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"when the new Congress starts in January ) .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"As it stands now ,","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"Republicans need Flake ' s vote","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"to pass any nominations out of the 11-10 Judiciary panel for floor consideration .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell does have the ability","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"to simply move these nominations himself ,","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"but so far he has not seemed interested in making this practice a habit .","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"Similarly in the Senate , Republicans ' slim 51-49 majority means","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"that Flake ' s defection could be enough","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"to help sink a nomination ,","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"or at the very least trigger a tie-breaker .","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"In the case of Farr , Democrats have mounted an aggressive push","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"to block his nomination .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"Given Flake ' s current stance ,","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"if they can convince just one more Republican to switch over ,","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"they could successfully take it down .","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"Flake , along with Sens . Chris Coons","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"( D-DE )","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"and Cory Booker","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"( D-NJ ) ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"attempted for the second time to schedule a floor vote on the bill","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"protecting Mueller","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"on Wednesday ,","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"but it was blocked by Sen. Mike Lee ,","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"who argued","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"that the legislation was unconstitutional","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"( a longstanding conservative argument ,","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"explained by ' s Tara Golshan here ) .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"The bill would ensure","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"that Mueller could only be fired by a Senate-confirmed DOJ official","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"and enable the special counsel to review any firing .","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"Many lawmakers see this legislation as increasingly more crucial in the wake of Attorney General Jeff Sessions ' s departure and Trump ' s ongoing critiques of the Mueller probe .","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"McConnell , however , has said","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"he doesn ' t see any threat","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"of Trump firing Mueller ,","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"and he indicated Tuesday","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"that he would \" probably block \" the bill from coming to the floor","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"if Flake pushed it a second time .","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"On the other hand , Majority Whip John Cornyn has previously signaled","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"that there could be an openness","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"to considering the legislation","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"to keep things moving on judicial nominees ,","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"especially as the Senate seeks to wrap business up toward the end of the year .","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"If existing nominees don ' t get confirmed","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"before this congressional term concludes ,","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"they will have to be renominated by the White House in the new year .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"McConnell has emphasized","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"that getting as many nominees through as possible is one of his key priorities this term and the next .","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"This isn ' t the first occasion","depth":4},{"id":98,"text":"that Flake has threatened to withhold his support for judicial nominees .","depth":4},{"id":99,"text":"He did something similar before","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"to prompt consideration of a measure on tariffs ,","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"though he ultimately relented","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"after the Senate voted on a purely symbolic effort .","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"This time , though , he says","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"he ' ll only change course","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"once the Senate votes on a binding bill .","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"Now , it ' s up to McConnell .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":213,"left":148,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nu